# Terraform Best Practices - Week 1

## 1. Project Structure

project/
├── main.tf # Primary resources
├── variables.tf # Input variables
├── outputs.tf # Output values
├── providers.tf # Provider configuration
├── backend.tf # Remote state config
├── versions.tf # Version constraints
├── terraform.tfvars # Variable values
└── modules/ # Reusable modules
text


## 2. Naming Conventions
✅ Use descriptive resource names
✅ Follow snake_case for resources
✅ Use consistent tagging
✅ Include environment in names

## 3. State Management
✅ Always use remote state
✅ Enable state locking
✅ Backup state regularly
✅ Limit state access
✅ Use workspaces for environments

## 4. Code Organization
✅ One resource per service
✅ Use modules for reusability
✅ Separate environments
✅ Use locals for calculations
✅ Implement variable validation

## 5. Security Practices
✅ Never commit secrets
✅ Use IAM roles properly
✅ Enable encryption
✅ Implement least privilege
✅ Regular security scans

## 6. Performance Tips
✅ Use count/for_each for multiple resources
✅ Parallelize resource creation
✅ Optimize provider configuration
✅ Use data sources wisely
✅ Minimize provisioner usage

## 7. Testing & Validation
✅ Always run terraform validate
✅ Use terraform fmt
✅ Implement plan review
✅ Test destroy operations
✅ Use policy as code

## 8. Collaboration
✅ Use version control
✅ Implement code reviews
✅ Document changes
✅ Use consistent workflows
✅ Share modules

## 9. Cost Management
✅ Use cost estimation tools
✅ Implement budgets
✅ Clean up test resources
✅ Monitor usage
✅ Rightsize resources

## 10. Monitoring & Maintenance
✅ Enable logging
✅ Set up alerts
✅ Regular updates
✅ Backup configurations
✅ Disaster recovery plan